  "strategy": [
    "Alternate between short forward moves and scanning rotations in clear areas to maximize marker detection.",
    "Upon detecting the marker, immediately switch to marker tracking and approach behaviors.",
    "If the marker is lost during tracking, perform a full scan to reacquire it.",
    "React to obstacles with safe recovery actions (move backward, rotate) and always scan before resuming exploration.",
    "Prioritize rotate_clockwise for obs_left and rotate_counterclockwise for obs_right to avoid oscillations.",
    "Never allow move_forward from obs_front; always require a recovery step.",
    "When marker_close is detected, transition to a terminal stop state to safely complete the task.",
    "Ensure all uncontrollable events are handled in every state, and only one controllable is enabled per state (except obs_front for recovery).",
    "Helper commit states enforce one-shot actions and prevent infinite controllable loops."
  ]
